data.name: NumLFixerDescription.Text
data.value: I don't know about you, but I don't even know why we CAN disable Num-Lock. If you have a number pad, it should be NUMBERS. Enabling this conntrol starts a watcher process that continually monitors Num-Lock and if it sees that it's off, it forces it back ON. LIKE IT SHOULD BE!

data.name: CMDFixerDescription.Text
data.value: When you need to run commands in CMD, it's usually in a specific folder. Windows used to have an option when you CTRL+Right Click to show "Open CMD HERE" on a folder. This restores that function AND it's at administrative level.

data.name: F1FixerDescription.Text
data.value: Have you ever hit the F1 key by accident and had a distracting and unhelpful window or webpage open as a result. Windows set the F1 key to a generic help function that basically never helps and always gets in the way. Enable this control to disable that obnoxious design choice. Note that some programs still respond to F1 on their own accord, but this will stop the default Windows behavior in things like Windows Explorer at least.
